      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Difficult Conversation Prep"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "communication"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "difficult"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "communication"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "courage"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "If there's a difficult conversation you need to have, imagine approaching it from this grounded place. You don't have to have all the answers. You just need to be present, honest, and willing to listen. What would it feel like to enter that conversation with your breath as an anchor? You can return to your breath whenever things get hard."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_007"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Email Pause Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "work"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "email"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "pause"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "reactivity"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Before you send your next email, especially if it's charged or important, pause. Take one breath. Read it again. Does it say what you really mean? Is the tone what you intend? This tiny pause between impulse and action can save you from so much unnecessary conflict. One breath. That's all it takes."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_008"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Commute Consciousness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "commute"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "travel"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Your commute, whether it's walking down the hall or driving across town, can be a practice. Instead of rushing through it on autopilot or lost in worry, what if you used that time to be present? To notice your surroundings. To breathe consciously. To transition intentionally from one part of your day to another."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_009"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Active Listening Intention"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "relationships"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "listening"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "presence"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "connection"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Set an intention to really listen in your next conversation. Not planning your response while they're talking. Not fixing or advising unless asked. Just listening. Receiving their words with the same open awareness you've practiced here. This is a gift you can give someone. The gift of being truly heard."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_010"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Eating Mindfully"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "eating"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "savoring"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Your next meal or snack is an opportunity for practice. Even if just for the first three bites, can you eat with full attention? Notice the taste, texture, temperature. Chew slowly. Appreciate the nourishment. Eating is something you do every day. What if it became a moment of presence instead of something to rush through?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_011"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Frustration Response"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "challenges"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "frustration"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "pause"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "response"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "The next time you feel frustrated, see if you can catch it early. Notice the sensation in your body. The heat, the tightness, the speeding up. Then pause. Just for a moment. One breath before you react. This doesn't mean suppressing your frustration. It means choosing how you respond to it. That choice changes everything."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_012"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Boundary Setting"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "relationships"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "boundaries"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "self_care"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "no"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Think about a boundary you need to set or reinforce. Saying no to something. Protecting your time or energy. Boundaries aren't mean. They're necessary. What would it be like to set a boundary from this grounded, calm place? Not out of anger or resentment, but from clarity about what you need. You deserve to protect your well-being."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_013"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Technology Pause"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "technology"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "screens"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "pause"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Before you pick up your phone or open social media next time, pause. Ask yourself, do I really want to do this right now, or is it just habit? Am I looking for something specific, or scrolling to avoid feeling something? This pause gives you choice. Sometimes you'll still scroll, and that's okay. But at least it's conscious."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_014"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Compassionate Self-Talk"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "self_care"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "self_talk"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "compassion"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "kindness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice how you talk to yourself today. When you make a mistake or struggle with something, what's the tone of your inner voice? If it's harsh, see if you can soften it. Talk to yourself the way you'd talk to a good friend. With kindness, with patience, with understanding. You deserve your own compassion."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_015"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Walking Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "embodiment"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "walking"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "movement"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "embodiment"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "The next time you walk somewhere, even if it's just to another room, try walking with awareness. Feel your feet touching the ground. Notice your body moving through space. You don't have to walk slowly or weirdly. Just bring consciousness to something you do all the time. Walking becomes meditation."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_016"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Waiting as Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "waiting"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "patience"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "presence"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "The next time you're waiting, in line, for a call to connect, for a page to load, instead of immediately reaching for distraction, try just being present. Feel your breath. Notice your surroundings. Waiting doesn't have to be wasted time or frustration. It can be a gift of a few moments of presence."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_017"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Conflict De-escalation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "relationships"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "conflict"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "de_escalation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wisdom"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "If you find yourself in conflict today, remember that you can choose how to engage. You can pause. You can breathe. You can ask yourself what really matters here. Sometimes the best response is no response. Sometimes it's vulnerability instead of defensiveness. Your practice gives you options. Use them."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_018"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Task Transition Breathing"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "work"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "transitions"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "tasks"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "breath"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "When you finish one task and before you start another, take three breaths. Just three. This creates a tiny space between doing and doing. It helps you arrive fresh at each new thing instead of carrying the stress of the last thing forward. Three breaths. That's all."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_019"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Gratitude Before Sleep"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "sleep"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "gratitude"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "evening"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Tonight before you sleep, recall one thing you're grateful for from today. Just one. It doesn't have to be big. This practice bookends your day with awareness and appreciation. It's also easier to sleep when your mind isn't churning with problems. Gratitude gives your mind something gentler to rest on."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_020"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Tension Check-In"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "embodiment"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "tension"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "body_awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "release"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Set a reminder on your phone or computer to check in with your body a few times today. Where are you holding tension? Your shoulders? Your jaw? Your belly? Just noticing is powerful. If you can, soften that area. Take a breath into it. Your body will thank you for these small moments of care."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_021"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Repair After Conflict"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "relationships"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "repair"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "apology"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "healing"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "If you had a conflict or said something you regret, this practice can help you repair. Ground yourself first. Then reach out, not from guilt or defensiveness, but from genuine care. Apologize if needed. Listen to their experience. Repairing relationships takes courage, but it's worth it. You can do hard things."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_022"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Morning Intention Setting"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "morning"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "intention"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "day"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Tomorrow morning, before you pick up your phone or start your day, take a moment to set an intention. Not a big goal or plan. Just one quality you want to bring to your day. Patience. Curiosity. Kindness. Presence. One word. Let that word guide you. Return to it when things get hard."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_023"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Creative Block Release"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "work"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "creativity"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "blocks"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "flow"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "If you're facing a creative block or stuck on a problem, step away and practice what you learned here. Let your nervous system calm. Stop forcing. The answer often comes when you stop trying so hard. Your unconscious mind works on problems while you rest. Trust the process."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_024"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Celebration Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "self_care"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "celebration"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wins"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "acknowledgment"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "When you accomplish something today, even something small, pause and acknowledge it. Don't immediately move to the next thing on your list. Take three seconds to say good job or I did it. Celebrating small wins isn't indulgent. It's necessary. It trains your brain to notice what's going well."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_025"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Compassionate Noticing"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "self_care"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "noticing"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "compassion"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "patterns"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "As you go through your day, practice compassionate noticing. Notice your patterns without judgment. I always tense my shoulders when I'm stressed. I reach for my phone when I'm uncomfortable. I avoid certain conversations. Just notice. Awareness is the first step to change. But it only works if it's kind."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_026"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Energy Management"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "work"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "energy"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "pacing"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "sustainability"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice your energy throughout the day. When do you feel most alive and focused? When does your energy dip? Can you structure your day to work with your natural rhythms instead of against them? Do challenging work when you're fresh. Rest when you need to. You're not a machine. Honor your human needs."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_027"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Receiving Compliments"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "relationships"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "receiving"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "compliments"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "worthiness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "The next time someone compliments you or thanks you, practice simply receiving it. Don't deflect. Don't minimize. Don't immediately return one. Just say thank you and let it in. You deserve appreciation. You don't have to earn it or qualify it. Just receive it. This is a radical practice for many of us."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_028"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Physical Movement Breaks"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "embodiment"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "movement"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "breaks"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "body"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Set an intention to move your body a few times today. Not exercise necessarily. Just movement. Stretch. Walk. Roll your shoulders. Shake out your hands. Your body isn't meant to be still for hours. Small movement breaks reset your nervous system and help you think more clearly. Give yourself permission to move."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_029"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Phone-Free Meals"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "phones"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "eating"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "presence"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Try having one meal today without your phone. No scrolling, no checking, no distraction. Just you and your food. If you're with others, just you and them. If you're alone, just you and your own company. Notice how it feels. Presence during meals is both ancient wisdom and radical resistance to modern life."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_030"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Saying Yes to Rest"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "self_care"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "rest"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "permission"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "care"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "If your body asks for rest today, see if you can say yes. Not later. Not after you finish everything. Now. Rest doesn't have to be earned. It's not a reward for productivity. It's a biological need. You deserve to rest simply because you're alive. What would it be like to trust that and act on it?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_031"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Micro-Joy Noticing"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "joy"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "noticing"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "appreciation"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Train yourself to notice micro-moments of joy today. The first sip of something you like. Sun on your face. A good song. Someone laughing. These moments are everywhere, but we miss them when we're on autopilot. What you pay attention to grows. Pay attention to joy. Let it accumulate."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_032"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Difficult Emotion Befriending"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "challenges"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "emotions"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "difficulty"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "acceptance"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "If a difficult emotion arises today, try meeting it with curiosity instead of resistance. What does this feeling want me to know? What does it need? Emotions aren't the enemy. They're messengers. You don't have to like them or want them to stay. But you can listen to what they're trying to tell you."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_033"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Evening Wind-Down"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "daily_life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "evening"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wind_down"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "transition"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Create an evening wind-down routine that signals to your body it's time to rest. Dim the lights. Put away screens. Do something gentle. Stretch, read, listen to quiet music. Your nervous system needs time to transition from day to night, from doing to being. Give yourself that transition time."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "integ_034"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Bringing It All With You"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wholeness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "presence"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Everything you've practiced here, the breathing, the awareness, the compassion, the presence, it's all available to you all the time. You don't leave it behind when this session ends. It's part of you now. The more you practice, the more accessible it becomes. Until one day, you realize you're not practicing anymore. You're just living this way. And that's when everything changes."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \}\cf12 \
  \cf11 ]\cf12 \
