    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_012"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Body Wisdom"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "somatic_intelligence"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "body"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "intuition"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wisdom"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Your body holds wisdom that your thinking mind doesn't always have access to. Drop your awareness into your body and ask, What do I need right now? Don't think about the answer. Feel for it. Let your body's wisdom rise up without forcing it. Trust what emerges."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_013"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Support Recognition"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "gratitude"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "support"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "connection"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "gratitude"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Think of one person who has supported you recently. Maybe they helped you with something concrete, or maybe they just listened. Let yourself feel what it's like to be supported. You don't have to do everything alone. Connection is part of being human."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_014"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "The Enough-ness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "self_acceptance"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "enough"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "worthiness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "acceptance"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "What if you are already enough, exactly as you are? Not when you accomplish more, change something, or become better. But right now, in this moment. Can you let that possibility in, even just a little? You are enough. You have always been enough."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_015"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Transition Awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "presence"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "transitions"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "presence"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "You're in a transition right now, moving from whatever you were doing before into this practice. Transitions happen all day long. We rarely pause to notice them. What does this particular transition feel like? How do you arrive in new moments?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_016"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Resistance Check"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "resistance"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "acceptance"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "flow"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Is there anything you're resisting right now? Maybe a feeling, a situation, even this practice itself? Resistance is natural. Notice it without making it wrong. What would it be like to soften around what you're resisting, even just one percent? Acceptance doesn't mean you like it. It just means you're meeting reality as it is."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_017"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Future Self Connection"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "intention"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "future"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "intention"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "self"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine yourself a few hours from now, after you've finished this practice. What would that future version of you want to thank the current you for doing? Sometimes we need to care for our future selves the way we'd care for someone we love. This practice is a gift you're giving yourself."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_018"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Quiet Celebration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "self_acknowledgment"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "acknowledgment"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "celebration"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wins"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "You showed up for yourself today. That matters. Even if nothing else went right, even if you're struggling, you made space for this. That's worth acknowledging. Take a moment to quietly celebrate yourself for being here."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_019"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Sensation Inventory"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "somatic_awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "sensation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "body"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "awareness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice the sensations in your body right now without trying to name them as good or bad. Temperature. Pressure. Texture. Movement. Energy. Your body is always sending you information through sensation. Right now, what is it communicating?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_020"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "The Gift of Pause"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "spaciousness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "pause"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "rest"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "spaciousness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "In a world that values constant doing, pausing is a radical act. Right now, you're practicing the art of pause. Nothing needs to be accomplished. Nothing needs to be fixed. This moment of simply being is enough. Can you let yourself receive this gift?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_021"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Anchor Point"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "grounding"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "grounding"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "anchor"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "stability"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "When everything feels chaotic or overwhelming, having an anchor point helps. It might be your breath, the feeling of your feet on the ground, or the sensation of your hands resting. Choose an anchor point right now. Something steady you can return to whenever you need stability."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_022"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Release Without Effort"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "letting_go"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "release"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "letting_go"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "ease"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Letting go doesn't require effort. It's actually the opposite. It's about stopping the effort of holding on. Is there something you've been gripping tightly? A worry, a tension, an expectation? What would it feel like to simply loosen your grip, even a little? You don't have to force anything. Just allow."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_023"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Being Held"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "support"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "support"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "held"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "safety"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice what's supporting you right now. The chair or floor beneath you. The air surrounding you. Gravity itself holding you. You are being held, always. Even when you feel alone, the earth is supporting you. Let yourself feel that support, even for just a moment."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_024"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Inner Resource Recognition"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "strength"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "resources"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "strength"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "resilience"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Think of a time when you successfully navigated something difficult. It doesn't have to be major. What inner resources did you draw on? Patience? Courage? Creativity? Those resources are still within you right now. They don't disappear. Acknowledge them. They're part of who you are."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_025"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "The Return"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "return"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "transition"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "As you prepare to return to your day, notice how you feel now compared to when you began. Something has shifted, even if it's subtle. You've given yourself the gift of attention. Carry this quality of presence with you. It's available whenever you need it."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_026"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Permission to Rest"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "self_care"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "rest"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "permission"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "care"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "When was the last time you gave yourself permission to truly rest? Not just sleep, but real rest. Rest from striving, from improving, from becoming. What would it feel like to rest right now, even for a moment? You don't have to earn rest. It's your birthright."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_027"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Witnessing Change"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "impermanence"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "change"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "impermanence"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "flow"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Everything is always changing. Your thoughts come and go. Your breath moves in and out. Sensations arise and fade. Even this moment is already becoming the past. What does it feel like to witness this constant flow of change? There's something freeing about remembering that nothing stays the same."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_028"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Heart Check-In"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "emotional_awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "heart"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "emotions"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "checking_in"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Place your attention in your heart space. Not your physical heart, but the center of your chest where you feel things emotionally. What's there right now? Openness? Tightness? Warmth? Heaviness? You don't need to change what you find. Just acknowledge it. Your heart is always speaking. Are you listening?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_029"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "The Ordinary Extraordinary"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "appreciation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "ordinary"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "appreciation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wonder"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Look around at something completely ordinary. Maybe a cup, a chair, a plant. Really look at it. Notice its colors, textures, shapes. Everything ordinary becomes extraordinary when we give it our full attention. What do you notice that you've never noticed before?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_030"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Your Why"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "purpose"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "purpose"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "meaning"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "intention"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Why did you choose to be here right now? What brought you to this practice? There are infinite things you could be doing, and yet you're here. That choice matters. What are you hoping for? What do you need? Let yourself connect with your deeper why."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_031"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Surrender Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "letting_go"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "surrender"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "trust"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "release"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Surrender doesn't mean giving up. It means releasing your grip on outcomes you can't control. What would it feel like to surrender right now? To stop fighting and simply trust the process? This doesn't mean you become passive. It means you stop exhausting yourself trying to control the uncontrollable."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_032"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Beginner's Mind"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "openness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "curiosity"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "openness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "fresh_eyes"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "What if you could experience this moment with fresh eyes? As if you've never experienced anything like it before. Beginner's mind means approaching life with curiosity instead of assumptions. Right now, what would change if you didn't think you knew what to expect? What might you discover?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_033"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "The Unspoken"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 75\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "intuition"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "knowing"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "unspoken"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Sometimes we know things we haven't put into words yet. There's something unspoken in you right now. Maybe it's a feeling, an intuition, a knowing. You don't have to name it or explain it. Just acknowledge that it's there. The unspoken has wisdom too."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "refl_034"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Coming Home"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 60\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "home"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "belonging"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "return"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Home isn't just a place. It's a feeling. A sense of belonging. Right now, as you connect with your breath and your body, you're coming home to yourself. No matter where you are physically, you can always return to this inner home. You belong here. You always have."\cf12 \
