    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_001"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Stress as Object"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "stress"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "transformation"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine your stress as a physical object. What does it look like? What color is it? What shape? How heavy is it? Now imagine you can pick it up and examine it from all sides. You don't have to do anything with it yet. Just look at it. Notice what happens when you can see your stress as something separate from you, something you can observe."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_002"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Future Memory"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "perspective_shift"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "future"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "perspective"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "gratitude"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you're looking back on this exact moment from five years in the future. What would your future self want to tell you about this time in your life? What would they say mattered? What would they say didn't matter as much as you thought? Sometimes the future gives us perspective the present can't."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_003"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Compassionate Observer"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "perspective_shift"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "compassion"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "self_view"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "kindness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine someone who loves you unconditionally is watching you live your life. Not judging, just witnessing with complete compassion. They see your struggles, your efforts, your pain, your trying. What would they want you to know? What would they say about how you're doing? Can you see yourself through their loving eyes, even for a moment?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_004"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Mountain Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "mountain"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "stability"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "weather"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you are a mountain. Solid, ancient, unshakeable. Weather moves around you. Storms come and go. Sun and rain, snow and wind. But you remain. You don't fight the weather. You simply allow it to pass. Your thoughts and emotions are like this weather. They move through you, but they don't change who you fundamentally are. You are the mountain."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_005"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Phoenix Rising"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "transformation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "transformation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "rebirth"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "resilience"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Think of something in your life that has ended or died. A relationship, a job, a dream, a version of yourself. Now imagine that ending as ashes. From those ashes, what is rising? What new thing is being born from what was lost? The phoenix doesn't return as the same bird. It becomes something new. What are you becoming?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_006"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "River of Life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "flow"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "river"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "acceptance"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine your life is a river. Sometimes it flows fast and turbulent. Sometimes slow and calm. Sometimes it hits rocks and has to move around them. But it always keeps flowing. You can't make the river go backwards. You can't stop it. You can only flow with it. What would it be like to trust the river instead of fighting it?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_007"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Inner Child Meeting"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "inner_work"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "inner_child"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "healing"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "care"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine meeting yourself as a child. You at seven or eight years old. They're sitting there looking at you. What do they need to hear from you? What comfort, what reassurance, what love can you offer them? Now imagine they have something to tell you too. What wisdom does your child self have for you? What have you forgotten that they remember?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_008"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Burden Release"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "release"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "burden"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "freedom"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you've been carrying a heavy backpack filled with stones. Each stone represents a burden. A worry, a responsibility, a pain, something you're holding that isn't yours to carry. One by one, imagine taking out the stones that don't belong to you. Feel the weight lifting. You don't have to carry everything. What can you put down?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_009"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Safe Haven"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "safety"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "sanctuary"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "refuge"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine a place, real or imagined, where you feel completely safe. What does it look like? What colors, textures, sounds, smells? Who or what is there with you? What makes this place feel so safe? Spend time here in your imagination. This place exists inside you. You can return to it anytime you need refuge."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_010"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Wise Elder Self"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "perspective_shift"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "wisdom"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "elder"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "guidance"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine yourself as a very old person at the end of a long, well-lived life. This elder version of you has seen it all, survived it all, learned it all. They're looking at your current situation with wisdom and perspective. What advice do they have for you? What do they know that you don't know yet? Listen to your elder self."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_011"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Garden of Self"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "growth"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "nurture"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "tending"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine your inner life is a garden. What's growing there? Are there flowers, weeds, overgrown areas, bare patches? What needs water and attention? What needs to be pruned? What seeds do you want to plant? You are both the garden and the gardener. How do you want to tend to yourself?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_012"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Door of Possibility"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "transformation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "possibility"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "choice"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "future"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine standing in front of a door. On the other side is the life you want, the version of yourself you're becoming. The door isn't locked. You can open it anytime. What's stopping you from opening it? Fear? Unworthiness? Uncertainty? Notice what's in the way. You don't have to open the door today. Just notice what keeps it closed."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_013"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Ocean Depths"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "depth"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "calm"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "ocean"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you are the ocean. On the surface, there might be waves, storms, turbulence. But deep below the surface, there is stillness. Complete calm. No matter what happens on the surface, the depths remain peaceful. You are both the surface and the depths. Can you drop down into your own depths, where peace is always waiting?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_014"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Museum of Your Life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "perspective_shift"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "perspective"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "life_review"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "meaning"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine walking through a museum dedicated to your life. Each room contains artifacts from different chapters. Your childhood, your relationships, your struggles, your victories. You're walking through as a visitor, not as the person who lived it. What stands out? What matters more than you thought? What matters less? This museum is your legacy. What story does it tell?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_015"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Tree of Life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "growth"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "roots"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "connection"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you are a tree. Your roots go deep into the earth, drawing nourishment, stability, connection to something larger than yourself. Your trunk is strong, weathered by storms but still standing. Your branches reach toward the sky, toward light and possibility. Feel yourself as this tree. Rooted and reaching. Grounded and growing. Both at once."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_016"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Healing Light"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "healing"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "light"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "energy"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine a warm, gentle light entering your body. You can choose the color. This light is healing, loving, compassionate. It moves through your body, finding any places of pain, tension, or darkness. It doesn't fight the darkness. It simply fills the space with light. Notice where the light goes. Notice what it illuminates."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_017"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Two Paths"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "choice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "choice"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "paths"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "decision"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you're standing at a fork in the road. Two paths stretch before you. One path represents continuing as you are. The other represents change, growth, risk. Walk a little way down each path in your imagination. What does each one feel like? What do you see? You don't have to choose right now. Just explore. Get to know both possibilities."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_018"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Balloon Release"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "release"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "letting_go"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "release"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "freedom"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you're holding a balloon. Written on it is something you need to let go of. A worry, a regret, a burden, a grudge. Feel the weight of holding onto it. Now imagine releasing the balloon. Watch it float up and away, getting smaller and smaller until it disappears. You can let go. It's safe to let go."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_019"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Mirror of Truth"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "inner_work"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "truth"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "self_seeing"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "honesty"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine looking into a special mirror that shows you absolute truth. Not harsh judgment, but honest, compassionate truth. What do you see? What truth about yourself are you ready to acknowledge? This mirror shows you both your wounds and your beauty. Both your fears and your courage. Can you look at yourself with this kind of honesty and compassion?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_020"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Safe House"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "safety"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "protection"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "refuge"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine building a house inside yourself, a room where you're completely safe. What does it look like? What's inside it? Who or what is allowed in, and what stays outside? This is your sanctuary. Your nervous system knows it's here. When the world feels overwhelming, you can retreat to this internal safe house. Build it strong and fill it with everything that comforts you."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_021"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Witness Stand"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "perspective_shift"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "witness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "observation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "distance"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you're sitting in a comfortable chair, watching your life like a movie. You're the witness, not the actor. From this perspective, you can see patterns you couldn't see when you were in the middle of things. What do you notice about your character in this movie? What do they keep doing? What do they really need? Witnessing creates distance. Distance creates choice."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_022"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Radio Dial"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "attention"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "choice"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "focus"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine your attention is like a radio dial. Right now, what station are you tuned to? Worry FM? Past Regrets Radio? Anxiety Network? Notice you can actually turn the dial. You can choose what you tune into. What station would serve you better right now? Peace, presence, possibility? You have more control over your attention than you think."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_023"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Alchemist's Laboratory"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "transformation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "alchemy"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "transformation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "transmutation"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you're an alchemist with the power to transform one thing into another. You can take your pain and transmute it into wisdom. Your fear into courage. Your anger into boundaries. Your grief into love. What do you most need to transform right now? You already have everything you need for this alchemy. The transformation is already beginning."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_024"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Constellation of People"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "connection"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "connection"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "support"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "community"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine all the people who have ever loved you or supported you, standing around you in a circle. Some might have died. Some you've lost touch with. But their care for you still exists. Feel yourself held by this constellation of love. You are not alone. You have never been alone. This circle of support is always around you, even when you can't see it."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_025"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Sculptor of Self"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "growth"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "creation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "becoming"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "art"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you are both the sculptor and the sculpture. You're creating yourself with each choice, each thought, each action. What are you sculpting? What parts are you emphasizing? What parts are you smoothing away? You get to decide what you're creating. This is your art. Your life is your masterpiece in progress."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_026"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Armor Removal"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "vulnerability"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "armor"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "protection"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "vulnerability"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you're wearing armor. Heavy plates that protect you but also weigh you down. Each piece represents a defense mechanism. Sarcasm, perfectionism, people-pleasing, numbness. Imagine carefully removing one piece of armor. Just one. What would it feel like to be a little less defended? A little more vulnerable? Vulnerability isn't weakness. It's courage."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_027"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Timeline Walk"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "perspective_shift"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "time"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "life_review"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "perspective"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you can walk along a timeline of your life. Past, present, and future laid out before you. Walk to a difficult moment in your past. Now look back at it from where you are today. Notice you survived it. You made it through. Now walk forward into your future. What do you want your future self to look back and see? You're creating that future right now."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_028"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Keys to Freedom"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "liberation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "freedom"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "liberation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "unlocking"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine you're holding a ring of keys. Each key unlocks a different cage you've been living in. A cage of obligation, of fear, of perfectionism, of others' expectations. Choose one key. One cage you're ready to unlock. You don't have to leave the cage yet if you're not ready. Just unlock the door. Know that you can leave whenever you choose."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_029"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Book of Your Life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "perspective_shift"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "story"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "narrative"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "authorship"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine your life is a book and you're the author. What chapter are you in right now? What's the title of this chapter? How does it fit into the larger story? Remember, you're still writing. This chapter isn't the whole book. The ending hasn't been written yet. You get to decide where the story goes from here."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_030"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Inner Circle"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "inner_work"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "parts"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wholeness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine all the different parts of yourself sitting in a circle. The scared part, the angry part, the sad part, the joyful part, the wise part. They're all here. None are bad. They all have something to offer. What if you could listen to each one without judgment? What if they could work together instead of fighting? You contain multitudes. Can you make peace between all your parts?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_031"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Phoenix Egg"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "potential"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "potential"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "becoming"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "emergence"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine there's something inside you waiting to hatch. A new version of yourself. A new possibility. It's not ready yet, but you can feel it growing, taking shape. What wants to be born through you? What's incubating in the darkness, gathering strength? Be patient with your own becoming. Everything emerges in its own time."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_032"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Web of Impact"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "connection"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "impact"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "ripples"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "meaning"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine every kind thing you've ever done sending out ripples. Every smile, every help offered, every moment of patience. These ripples touch other people, who create their own ripples. You can't see the full web of your impact, but it's vast. Your life matters more than you know. Your kindness travels farther than you can imagine."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "thought_033"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Season of Life"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "acceptance"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
