    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_025"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Skin Boundary"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "sensation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "skin"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "boundary"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "containment"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice your skin, the boundary of your body. It contains you. It protects you. It's constantly sensing your environment. Feel the sensation of air or fabric against your skin. Your skin knows where you end and the world begins. This boundary is important. It keeps you safe. It defines you as separate. Appreciate it."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_026"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Breath in Ribs"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "breath_body"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "ribs"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "expansion"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "breath"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Place your hands on the sides of your ribcage. Feel your ribs expand with each inhale, release with each exhale. Your ribs are like a flexible cage, protecting your heart and lungs while allowing them to move. Breathe into your side ribs. Feel them expand three-dimensionally. This is breath at its fullest."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_027"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Inner Smile"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "face"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 90\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "face"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "softness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "kindness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Bring a very soft, subtle smile to your face. Not a big grin, just the tiniest lift at the corners of your mouth. Notice how this tiny shift changes your whole face, even your whole mood. Now bring that smile inside. Smile at your heart. Smile at your belly. Smile at yourself from the inside. This is self-kindness."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_028"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Legs and Support"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "regional"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "legs"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "support"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "strength"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice your legs. Your thighs, your knees, your calves, your ankles. These are the pillars that support you. They carry you through your day. They're strong even when you don't feel strong. Feel the power in your legs. The muscles, the bones, the capability. Your legs support you. They've got you."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_029"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Neck and Head Balance"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "regional"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "neck"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "head"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "balance"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Your head weighs about as much as a bowling ball. Your neck supports this weight all day. Notice your neck now. Is it tense? Is your head balanced on top of your spine, or are you pushing it forward? Imagine your head floating slightly up, lengthening your neck. Let your neck do less work. Let your head balance."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_030"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Body Gratitude"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "appreciation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "gratitude"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "appreciation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "love"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Take a moment to thank your body. Not for how it looks, but for what it does. It breathes for you. It heals your wounds. It digests your food. It moves you through the world. Even when you criticize it, it keeps working for you. Can you feel grateful for this body, just as it is? It's doing its best for you."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_031"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Shoulder Blade Awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "regional"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 120\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "shoulder_blades"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "upper_back"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wings"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice your shoulder blades, those flat bones on your upper back. Some traditions call them your wings. Can you feel them? Try gently squeezing them together, then releasing. They support your arms, your gestures, your reaching. They're part of your back body, often forgotten. Bring awareness to your shoulder blades. Feel your wings."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_032"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Organs Appreciation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "depth"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "organs"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "internal"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "function"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Think about your organs working right now. Your heart pumping blood. Your lungs exchanging oxygen. Your stomach digesting. Your liver filtering. Your kidneys cleaning. All of this happening without you having to think about it. Your organs are intelligent. They know their jobs. Can you feel appreciation for this invisible, constant labor happening inside you?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_033"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Energy Body Sense"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "sensation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 150\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "energy"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "subtle"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "aliveness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Beyond your physical body, can you sense an energy body? A field of aliveness that extends slightly beyond your skin? Some call this your aura, your energy field, your presence. It might feel like warmth, tingling, expansion, or just a sense of being bigger than your physical form. You're not just meat and bones. You're energy. You're light."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "body_034"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Complete Body Integration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "full_body"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 180\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wholeness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "complete"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Now feel your entire body as one whole system. Not separate parts, but one integrated being. From the crown of your head to the soles of your feet. All of it breathing together, living together, being together. This is you. Complete. Whole. Alive. You are here. You are embodied. This body is your home. Welcome home."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \}\cf12 \
  \cf11 ]\cf12 \
