  \cf13 "exercises"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_001"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Breath Anchor"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 180\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "breath"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "focus"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "foundation"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Find your breath wherever you feel it most clearly. Maybe at your nostrils, in your chest, or in your belly. Rest your attention there gently. When your mind wanders, and it will, simply notice and return to the breath. No judgment. Just return. The breath is always here. It's a reliable anchor in the changing stream of experience."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_002"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Open Awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "spacious"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "receptive"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Instead of focusing on any one thing, let your awareness be wide and open. Notice whatever arises. Sounds, sensations, thoughts, emotions. Don't chase anything. Don't push anything away. Just receive whatever comes. Like sitting by a river watching it flow. You are the aware space in which everything appears and disappears."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_003"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Loving Kindness Foundation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "heart_practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "metta"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "love"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "kindness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Begin by directing kindness toward yourself. Silently offer yourself these phrases: May I be safe. May I be healthy. May I be happy. May I live with ease. Feel the intention behind the words, even if the feelings don't come easily. Now extend these wishes to someone you love. Then to someone neutral. Then to someone difficult. Then to all beings everywhere. Let kindness radiate out."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_004"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Body Sensation Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "somatic"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "body"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "sensation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "somatic"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Bring your attention to physical sensations in your body. Not thinking about your body, but actually feeling it. Notice pressure, temperature, tingling, tension, relaxation. Sensations are constantly arising and passing. Stay with direct experience. When thoughts come, notice them and return to sensation. The body is always in the present moment."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_005"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Counting Breaths"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "concentration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 180\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "counting"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "focus"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "breath"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Count your breaths from one to ten. Inhale one, exhale one. Inhale two, exhale two. When you reach ten, start over. If you lose count, start over. This seems simple but it's not easy. Your mind will wander. That's okay. That's the practice. Notice when you've wandered and begin again. Building concentration is like building a muscle."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_006"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Sound Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "sound"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "listening"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "awareness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Let sounds be the object of your meditation. Don't label them or create stories about them. Just hear them as pure sound. Near sounds and far sounds. Loud and soft. Continuous and intermittent. Notice the space between sounds. Sound arises in silence and returns to silence. You are the listening. The awareness that hears."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_007"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Noting Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "noting"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "labeling"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "clarity"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "As experiences arise, gently note them. Thinking. Feeling. Hearing. Seeing. Planning. Remembering. Itching. The note should be light, like a whisper. You're not getting caught in the content, just acknowledging what's happening. This creates a little space between you and your experience. You're not your thoughts. You're the awareness noticing them."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_008"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Compassion for Difficulty"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "heart_practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "compassion"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "difficult"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "suffering"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Bring to mind a difficulty you're facing. Not the worst thing, but something real. Notice where you feel it in your body. Now place your hand on your heart. Acknowledge this is suffering. This is hard. Offer yourself compassion. You might say: May I be kind to myself in this moment. May I give myself the compassion I need. Suffering is part of being human. You deserve kindness."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_009"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Breath and Space"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "breath"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "space"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "expansion"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice the space that breath moves through. The space in your nostrils, your throat, your lungs. Notice the space around your body. The space in the room. Breath moves through space. Sounds move through space. Thoughts arise in the space of awareness. Everything is held in space. You are space, aware of itself."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_010"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Walking Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "movement"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 360\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "walking"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "movement"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "steps"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Walk very slowly. Feel each component of the step. Lifting, moving, placing. Heel, ball, toe. Let your attention rest in your feet and legs. When your mind wanders, return to the sensation of walking. This can be done for a few steps or for many minutes. Walking becomes meditation. Each step is complete in itself. Each step is arrival."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_011"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Choiceless Awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "choiceless"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "open"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "receptive"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Don't choose what to pay attention to. Let attention move naturally to whatever is most prominent. Maybe it's breath for a while. Then a sound. Then a thought. Then a sensation. You're not directing. You're allowing. Witnessing whatever arises without preference. This is the mind in its natural, unconditioned state. Awake. Present. Free."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_012"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Gratitude Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "heart_practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "gratitude"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "appreciation"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "heart"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Bring to mind something or someone you're grateful for. Let yourself really feel the gratitude. Where do you feel it in your body? Maybe warmth in your chest. Maybe a softening. Stay with this feeling. Let it fill you. Now think of another thing. And another. Let gratitude build. Gratitude shifts everything. It opens the heart."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_013"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Silence Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "stillness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "silence"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "stillness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "quiet"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Rest in silence. Not the absence of sound, but the presence of stillness. Even when there are sounds, there is silence underneath. Even when there are thoughts, there is stillness beneath the thinking. You are not trying to achieve silence. You're recognizing the silence that's already here. The silence you are."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_014"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Mountain Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "mountain"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "stability"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "strength"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine yourself as a mountain. Solid, unmoving, majestic. Weather passes over you. Storms come and go. Seasons change. But you remain. Grounded. Stable. Dignified. Feel this mountain quality in your own body. Your body sitting like a mountain. Unchanging presence in the midst of change. This is your true nature. Unshakeable."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_015"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Breath Counting Advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "concentration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "counting"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "breath"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "precision"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Count only the exhales from one to ten. Stay with the full length of each breath. Notice the qualities of each breath. Some long, some short. Some smooth, some rough. Can you stay present for ten complete breaths without your mind wandering? If you can, you've developed significant concentration. If you can't, that's okay. Keep practicing."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_016"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Body of Light"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "visualization"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "light"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "energy"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "subtle"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Imagine your body is made of light. Not solid, but luminous. Breathing light in, breathing light out. Feel this radiance in every cell. You are not heavy or dense. You are light itself. This isn't just imagination. At the quantum level, you are mostly space and energy. Feel the truth of your light body."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_017"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Difficult Emotion Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "somatic"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "emotion"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "difficulty"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "courage"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "If a difficult emotion is present, turn toward it instead of away. Where do you feel it in your body? What's the sensation? Can you stay with it without trying to fix it or make it go away? Breathe with it. Make space for it. Emotions need to be felt to move through. Your willingness to feel is healing. You can handle this."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_018"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Breath at Nostrils"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "concentration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "nostrils"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "subtle"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "focus"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Feel the breath at the tip of your nose or just inside your nostrils. The cool air entering. The warm air leaving. This is a very precise point of focus. It requires concentration. Your mind will wander. Each time, return to this small area. The sensations are subtle. You're training your mind to be sensitive to subtle experience."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_019"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Loving Kindness Expanding"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "heart_practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 360\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "metta"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "expansion"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "boundless"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Begin with loving kindness for yourself. Then expand it to loved ones. To friends. To neutral people. To difficult people. To all beings in your neighborhood, your city, your country, the world. Let your heart expand to include everyone. All beings want to be happy. All beings want to be free from suffering. May all beings be well."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_020"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Emptiness Contemplation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "insight"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "emptiness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "insight"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "nature"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice that everything you experience is constantly changing. Thoughts arise and pass. Sensations come and go. Even your sense of self shifts. Nothing is solid or permanent. This isn't nihilistic. It's liberating. When you see that nothing has a fixed, solid self, you can relax your grip. You don't have to hold on so tight."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_021"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Present Moment Anchor"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 180\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "present"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "now"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "simple"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "The past is memory. The future is imagination. The only reality is this moment right now. Can you be here? Not thinking about being here. Actually being here. Feel your body. Hear the sounds. Notice you're breathing. This is it. This moment. This is all there ever is. Can you meet it fully?"\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_022"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Forgiveness Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "heart_practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "forgiveness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "release"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "healing"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Think of someone you need to forgive. This doesn't mean what they did was okay. It means you're releasing the weight of holding grudges. Say silently: I forgive you. I release this. I free myself. Now think of someone you need to ask forgiveness from. Say: I'm sorry. Please forgive me. Finally, forgive yourself. For all your mistakes. All your shortcomings. You're human. You deserve forgiveness."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_023"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Energy Body Scan"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "somatic"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "energy"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "subtle_body"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "chi"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Scan your body for energy sensations. Tingling, warmth, coolness, vibration, flow, blockage. This is your subtle body, your energy body. Some traditions call it chi or prana. Notice where energy is strong and where it's weak. Where it flows and where it's stuck. Your body is not just physical. It's energetic."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_024"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Just Sitting"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "stillness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 360\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "shikantaza"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "just_sitting"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "zen"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Sit. Just sit. No technique. No method. No trying to achieve anything. Not even trying to meditate. Just be here. Present. Awake. Alert but not efforting. This is shikantaza. Just sitting. The simplest practice and the hardest. Because there's nowhere to go. Nothing to do. Just this. Just now."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_025"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Awe Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "heart_practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "awe"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wonder"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "vastness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Bring to mind something that fills you with awe. The stars. The ocean. A mountain. The complexity of your own body. Let yourself feel small in the best way. Connected to something vast. Awe takes us out of our small concerns. It reminds us we're part of something immense. Let yourself be touched by wonder."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_026"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Death Contemplation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "insight"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "death"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "impermanence"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "urgency"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "You will die. This body will die. Everyone you love will die. This isn't morbid. It's reality. And it makes life precious. If you truly understood that your time is limited, how would you live? What would matter? What wouldn't? Death isn't the enemy. Forgetting death is. When you remember death, you remember to live."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_027"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Interconnection Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "insight"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "interconnection"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "dependent_arising"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "unity"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Nothing exists independently. Everything depends on everything else. The food you ate required sun, rain, soil, farmers, truckers. Your breath requires trees making oxygen. Your thoughts are influenced by everyone you've ever met. You're not separate. You're woven into the fabric of all life. Feel this interconnection. You belong to the whole."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_028"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Mudita Practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "heart_practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "mudita"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "joy"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "happiness"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Mudita is sympathetic joy. Happiness in others' happiness. Think of someone who's doing well. Someone who's happy. Instead of envy, can you feel genuine joy for them? May your happiness continue. May your success grow. This practice counters our tendency toward jealousy. There's enough happiness to go around. Your joy doesn't diminish mine."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_029"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Equanimity Meditation"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "heart_practice"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "equanimity"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "balance"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "acceptance"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Equanimity is wise balance. Not detachment or coldness, but accepting that you can't control everything. Things are as they are. People will do what they do. You can care deeply and still let go of outcomes. Say silently: All beings are responsible for their own happiness. I can love and still let go. I can care and still accept."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_030"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Return to Center"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "mindfulness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 180\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "beginner"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "center"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "home"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "return"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Your center is always here. No matter how far you wander into thought, worry, or distraction, you can always return. Come back to your breath. Come back to your body. Come back to now. This is home. This is center. You don't have to stay lost. The way back is always available. Just notice and return."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_031"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Witness Consciousness"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "insight"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "witness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "awareness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "observer"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Notice that you are aware. Aware of thoughts, sensations, emotions. But you're not those things. You're the awareness that knows them. This awareness is always present. It doesn't come and go. It's the constant background. Who is it that's aware? Can you find the one who's watching? Rest as that. Pure awareness itself."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_032"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Breath As Gateway"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "concentration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 240\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "breath"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "gateway"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "depth"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Use the breath as a gateway to deeper states. Follow each breath all the way in. All the way out. Let it become more subtle. More refined. As your attention steadies, the breath becomes quieter. The mind becomes quieter. You sink into deeper calm. Deeper stillness. The breath leads you home to silence."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_033"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Self-Inquiry"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "insight"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 300\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "advanced"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "self_inquiry"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "who_am_i"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "identity"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Ask yourself: Who am I? Not your name, your job, your story. Who is the one asking? Who is aware of awareness? This question can't be answered with thought. It points you to direct experience. Keep asking. Keep looking. Who am I? The answer is not in words. It's in the silence behind the question."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \},\cf12 \
    \cf11 \{\cf12 \
      \cf13 "id"\cf12 : \cf14 "med_034"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "name"\cf12 : \cf14 "Complete Integration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "category"\cf12 : \cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "duration_seconds"\cf12 : \cf15 360\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "difficulty"\cf12 : \cf14 "intermediate"\cf11 ,\cf12 \
      \cf13 "tags"\cf12 : \cf11 [\cf14 "integration"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "wholeness"\cf11 ,\cf12  \cf14 "completion"\cf11 ],\cf12 \
      \cf13 "text"\cf12 : \cf14 "Bring together everything you've practiced. Breath awareness. Body sensation. Open awareness. Loving kindness. Insight. It's all here. All available. You don't need to choose. Let it all be present. This is your practice. This is your path. You're not learning something new. You're remembering what you've always known. You're waking up to what you've always been."\cf12 \
    \cf11 \}\cf12 \
  \cf11 ]\cf12 \
